ACHIEVAS Entertainment has announced the signing of gospel singer, Jacinta Onuoha aka ‘Onyinye’. Speaking on the choice of signing a gospel singer to the outfit, the founder of Achievas Entertainment, Paul Cole Chiori disclosed that Onyinye was signed as a result of her singing prowess, her ability to compose songs, and her vocal power. He said, “Onyinye is much more than a singer who has all qualities needed of an artist to excel in the creative industry, she understands the craft, and above all her unique voice and texture will differentiate her from others.”   AVRS gets Police AIG’s assurance in war against audiovisual…     Lagos, Africa Film Academy to train 200 youths in filmmaking     Residents applaud unique programming as GOtv launches in…   Onyiye, who was discovered by Chiori, made her impact as a singer at a very tender age as a choir leader. As part of her building-up, while in school, Onyinye worked with a gospel evangelical group as a chorister where she ministered in schools like the University of Lagos, University of Benin, Kwara State University, and the Federal University of Technology Owerri amongst others. In 2018, Onyiye recorded a soundtrack for the movie The Island alongside Toka McBaror which received 10 nominations from Toronto International Nollywood Film Festival in Canada and won four different awards. While Onyinye is signed to Achievas Entertainment, she will be managed by the Undaground media outfit led by Daniel Cole Chiori.